s the first edition of the event to achieve full gender equality.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1145, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"the first edition\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1099}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"full gender equality\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1144}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China won 40 gold, 27 silver, and 24 bronze medals.\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1147, \"end\": 1152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9994722352330341, \"rank\": 0.00031050883224602945, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"40 gold\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"27 silver\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1175}, {\"ngram\": \"24 bronze medals\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1197}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 40 golds tied with the USA for the most, and the delegation's total of 91 overall medals set a new record for the country's best performance at an overseas Olympics.\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998723777035889, \"rank\": 0.00012669820204647708, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 40 golds\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"the delegation's total\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1270}, {\"ngram\": \"91 overall medals\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"a new record\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"the country's best performance\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"an oversea